WEBVTT

00:05.805 --> 00:08.742
<i>[light piano music]</i>

00:08.842 --> 00:13.413
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:13.513 --> 00:15.482
- You wanna do the stamp?

00:16.516 --> 00:17.751
- Approved or denied?

00:17.851 --> 00:19.152
- Mm.

00:22.389 --> 00:23.923
Uh-huh.

00:24.024 --> 00:25.258
Your homework done?

00:25.358 --> 00:26.860
Good.

00:28.194 --> 00:31.164
Well, you can...

00:31.231 --> 00:33.233
balance my checkbook.

00:46.379 --> 00:49.115
What?
- This check's gonna bounce.

00:49.215 --> 00:50.683
This one too.

00:51.718 --> 00:53.253
- No.

00:53.353 --> 00:54.921
Thanks, baby.

00:56.790 --> 00:58.058
[sighs]

01:09.903 --> 01:12.205
[line ringing]

01:12.272 --> 01:14.140
<i>- Hello.</i>
- Leon, it's Suzanné.

01:14.240 --> 01:15.241
<i>- Hey.</i>

01:15.308 --> 01:16.776
- I need
a couple hundred dollars.

01:16.876 --> 01:18.478
<i>- I paid my child support</i>
<i>this month.</i>

01:18.578 --> 01:21.648
- Yes, you completed your
court-ordered bare minimum,

01:21.748 --> 01:24.217
but I had to spend extra money
for Mia's birthday party,

01:24.284 --> 01:25.585
which is tomorrow, by the way.

01:25.652 --> 01:27.087
<i>- I know when it is.</i>

01:27.153 --> 01:29.456
<i>Just--I'm a little</i>
<i>strapped this month too.</i>

01:29.556 --> 01:31.558
- You know what?
Don't even bother coming.

01:31.624 --> 01:33.059
<i>- Hold on. Hold on.</i>

01:35.662 --> 01:37.097
- [exhales]

01:39.099 --> 01:41.000
I'm sorry you had
to hear that, baby.

01:41.101 --> 01:43.136
- Dad really can't come
to the party?

01:43.236 --> 01:45.472
- It would be better
if he didn't.

01:45.572 --> 01:47.307
Your father's trifling.

01:48.608 --> 01:49.943
But you know what?

01:50.009 --> 01:53.279
Your birthday party's
gonna be so fun, Mia.

01:53.346 --> 01:55.348
We're gonna go skating,

01:55.448 --> 01:57.584
and I got ice cream cake,

01:57.650 --> 02:00.186
and all your friends
are gonna be there.

02:00.286 --> 02:03.022
It's gonna be
the best one yet, baby.

02:03.123 --> 02:05.692
<i>- ♪ Working on</i>
<i>this dream with you ♪</i>

02:05.792 --> 02:08.027
<i>♪ Oh, baby ♪</i>

02:08.127 --> 02:09.496
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:09.596 --> 02:12.198
<i>♪ Wanna spend</i>
<i>my life with you ♪</i>

02:12.298 --> 02:13.366
<i>♪ Oh, baby ♪</i>

02:13.466 --> 02:15.135
- So, how did I do?

02:16.202 --> 02:17.470
- Oh.

02:17.537 --> 02:18.538
Hell yeah.

02:18.638 --> 02:20.006
Hang on.
Stay right there.

02:20.106 --> 02:21.474
- [laughs] Okay.

02:21.541 --> 02:23.376
- This is for
the permanent memory file.

02:23.476 --> 02:25.678
I am sending this to the cloud.

02:25.778 --> 02:26.946
- Wait,
what else is in the cloud?

02:27.013 --> 02:28.148
- Don't worry about it.

02:28.214 --> 02:29.349
- Wait,
don't take a photo here.

02:29.449 --> 02:30.483
That's not funny.
- Why'd you come

02:30.550 --> 02:31.885
all the way over here then?

02:31.985 --> 02:34.821
<i>- ♪ You've got a woman ♪</i>

02:34.888 --> 02:37.657
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:37.724 --> 02:41.060
<i>narrator: Mia Hines had</i>
<i>never had much faith in men.</i>

02:41.161 --> 02:44.164
<i>And for the most part,</i>
<i>men had proven her distrust</i>

02:44.230 --> 02:46.065
<i>to be well-founded.</i>

02:46.166 --> 02:48.835
<i>Suzanné Hayward had drilled it</i>
<i>into her daughter</i>

02:48.902 --> 02:51.738
<i>that men were</i>
<i>not only unreliable,</i>

02:51.838 --> 02:53.873
<i>but superfluous.</i>

02:53.973 --> 02:56.576
<i>As an adult,</i>
<i>she projected those qualities</i>

02:56.676 --> 02:58.077
<i>onto her boyfriends,</i>

02:58.178 --> 03:03.650
<i>whether or not they fit</i>
<i>that description.</i>

03:03.716 --> 03:05.385
<i>Marcus was the exception.</i>

03:05.485 --> 03:08.488
<i>He had been an eerily</i>
<i>perfect boyfriend.</i>

03:08.555 --> 03:11.157
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:11.224 --> 03:13.059
<i>Maybe too perfect.</i>

03:13.159 --> 03:16.062
<i>- ♪ Trust in me,</i>
<i>I'll set you free ♪</i>

03:16.162 --> 03:18.665
<i>♪ Come along and follow me ♪</i>
<i>[indistinct chatter]</i>

03:18.731 --> 03:20.767
- Hi, Mom.
<i>- Hey, baby.</i>

03:20.867 --> 03:21.935
<i>You have a minute?</i>

03:22.035 --> 03:23.269
- Yeah,
I have a couple minutes.

03:23.369 --> 03:26.072
Marcus is actually
on his way over.

03:26.172 --> 03:27.440
<i>- Again? Oh.</i>

03:27.540 --> 03:28.775
<i>He's practically</i>
<i>living over there now.</i>

03:28.875 --> 03:30.343
- Okay, well,
we split our time

03:30.410 --> 03:33.913
between both apartments
like a normal couple.

03:34.013 --> 03:35.782
<i>- Mm-hmm.</i>

03:35.882 --> 03:37.217
- Whatever.

03:37.283 --> 03:38.184
How are you?

03:38.251 --> 03:40.453
<i>- Oh, yeah, fine.</i>

03:40.553 --> 03:41.955
<i>Except...</i>

03:42.055 --> 03:44.924
<i>I lost the house.</i>

03:45.024 --> 03:47.026
- Oh, um...

03:49.395 --> 03:51.564
I'm sorry, Mom.

03:51.631 --> 03:54.434
<i>- Yeah, but we knew</i>
<i>this day was coming, honey.</i>

03:55.435 --> 03:56.636
<i>- How did this happen?</i>

03:56.736 --> 03:58.204
I thought your Mom
worked at a bank.

03:58.271 --> 04:00.974
- So what, Marcus?
She has unlimited cash flow?

04:01.074 --> 04:02.442
This may come
as a surprise to you,

04:02.542 --> 04:04.310
but not everybody's parents
are, like,

04:04.410 --> 04:06.279
responsible black professors.

04:06.379 --> 04:08.781
- That's--
that's not what I meant.

04:10.049 --> 04:11.317
- No, I know.

04:12.952 --> 04:14.954
My mom's never been
responsible with money.

04:15.054 --> 04:17.290
Her philosophy has always been,
"I should be making more."

04:17.390 --> 04:20.159
Not,
"I should be spending less."

04:20.260 --> 04:22.161
- Anything I can do to help?

04:22.262 --> 04:23.663
I can come down if you want.

04:23.763 --> 04:26.332
- I honestly have been
taking care of my mom

04:26.432 --> 04:29.502
since I was 10, and...

04:29.602 --> 04:30.503
I got it.

04:30.603 --> 04:32.505
- Well, I-I know you got it.

04:32.605 --> 04:36.009
But you shouldn't be
taking this on all by yourself,

04:36.109 --> 04:37.577
and...

04:39.279 --> 04:40.813
I wanna help.

04:41.848 --> 04:43.449
- You're sweet.

04:43.516 --> 04:46.185
Just let me go down there
and assess,

04:46.286 --> 04:47.854
and then I'll let you know.

04:47.954 --> 04:49.022
Okay?

04:49.122 --> 04:50.323
- Okay.

04:51.491 --> 04:54.494
<i>[light, sentimental music]</i>

04:54.594 --> 05:01.668
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:11.944 --> 05:14.213
<i>narrator: Though she came home</i>
<i>regularly,</i>

05:14.314 --> 05:17.116
<i>the house Mia grew up in</i>
<i>now more closely resembled</i>

05:17.183 --> 05:18.785
<i>an art installation.</i>

05:18.851 --> 05:22.188
<i>One that would soon be</i>
<i>broken down and boxed up,</i>

05:22.288 --> 05:25.792
<i>relegated forever</i>
<i>to the halls of memory.</i>

05:25.858 --> 05:26.893
- Mia?

05:26.993 --> 05:29.028
Baby. Oh.
- Hey.

05:29.128 --> 05:30.630
- I'm so glad you're here.

05:30.697 --> 05:32.398
- Yeah, it sucks it's under
these circumstances.

05:32.498 --> 05:35.568
- No, it's fine. It's fine.
It's all gonna be fine.

05:35.668 --> 05:37.670
My art's the only stuff
I wanna keep.

05:37.737 --> 05:38.905
The rest, just leave it.

05:39.005 --> 05:40.406
Let the new owners
deal with it.

05:40.506 --> 05:42.475
- Wait. What about my stuff?
- Well, yeah.

05:42.542 --> 05:44.577
Take your stuff too, Mia.
Of course.

05:44.677 --> 05:46.479
- To my studio in Brooklyn?

05:46.546 --> 05:47.814
- Are you mad at me?

05:47.880 --> 05:50.583
- No, Mom.
Did you buy a new car?

05:50.683 --> 05:52.919
- I had to do it before this
showed up on my credit report.

05:53.019 --> 05:54.887
- Are you gonna remember
to make the payments?

05:54.987 --> 05:57.990
- I pay my bills, Mia.
I'm not an idiot.

05:58.057 --> 06:00.393
I was underwater on this place,
sweetheart.

06:00.493 --> 06:02.495
Remember when I refinanced
to have money

06:02.562 --> 06:04.764
to help you through college?
Remember that?

06:04.864 --> 06:06.833
Well, I borrowed too much,
and then they never

06:06.899 --> 06:09.435
gave me the promotion
they promised me.

06:09.535 --> 06:11.270
- Mom, I'm sorry it just--

06:11.371 --> 06:13.039
it sucks
that you're losing the house

06:13.106 --> 06:15.842
and Dad still has
a fast-food empire.

06:15.908 --> 06:18.611
- Well, I wouldn't call it
an empire.

06:18.711 --> 06:20.279
- Yeah, but he still has money.

06:20.380 --> 06:22.515
- And I'm happy for him.

06:26.519 --> 06:28.020
[clears throat]

06:28.087 --> 06:29.789
- Damn, Mom.
Where are you going?

06:29.889 --> 06:32.458
- Houston's.
- With who?

06:32.558 --> 06:33.793
- Nunya.
- Nun--

06:33.893 --> 06:35.128
oh, you still doing Nunya?

06:35.228 --> 06:37.130
You're still doing that?
- Nunya business.

06:37.230 --> 06:38.965
- [laughs]

06:39.065 --> 06:40.600
- I see you found
the fruit punch.

06:40.700 --> 06:42.535
- Don't act like you
didn't put this out for me.

06:42.602 --> 06:45.071
- [laughs]
[phone chiming]

06:46.806 --> 06:48.741
- Hey, babe.
- Hey, Marcus.

06:48.808 --> 06:50.276
<i>- H-hi, Miss Hayward.</i>

06:50.376 --> 06:52.412
- Come on, Marcus.
I told you to call me Suzanné.

06:52.478 --> 06:53.579
<i>- I know.</i>

06:53.646 --> 06:55.915
<i>I'm old-fashioned, I guess.</i>

06:55.982 --> 06:57.784
- So old-fashioned
that you're shacking up

06:57.884 --> 06:59.051
with my daughter, huh?
- Mom.

06:59.118 --> 07:00.486
<i>- Uh, I mean, we--</i>

07:00.586 --> 07:02.388
<i>we don't--</i>
<i>we don't live together.</i>

07:02.455 --> 07:03.556
- Babe,
don't even worry about it.

07:03.623 --> 07:04.824
She's messing with you.

07:04.924 --> 07:05.825
- I am.

07:05.925 --> 07:07.493
Kinda.

07:07.593 --> 07:09.395
All right, honey.
Muah.

07:09.462 --> 07:10.630
Good to see you, Marcus.

07:10.730 --> 07:12.331
<i>- You too, Miss Hayward.</i>

07:12.432 --> 07:14.133
- Bye, Mom.
- Bye-bye.

07:14.233 --> 07:16.135
<i>- She's in a good mood</i>
<i>for someone losing her house.</i>

07:16.235 --> 07:18.738
- Yeah, well, that's because
I am doing everything.

07:18.805 --> 07:21.174
<i>- I can still come down.</i>
- No, it's okay.

07:21.274 --> 07:23.109
I'm using up all my sick days.

07:23.176 --> 07:24.444
I'm gonna try to come back
soon anyway,

07:24.510 --> 07:26.512
but I'll call you later.

07:26.612 --> 07:28.915
<i>- Okay, um, bye.</i>

07:28.981 --> 07:30.516
- Okay. Bye.

07:30.616 --> 07:33.619
<i>[instrumental R&B playing]</i>

07:33.686 --> 07:38.691
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:38.791 --> 07:40.626
[indistinct chatter]

07:40.693 --> 07:43.796
[giggling]

07:46.199 --> 07:49.335
[indistinct chatter]

07:52.438 --> 07:53.439
Dad?

07:53.506 --> 07:55.174
- [whispers] It's just--

07:55.274 --> 07:56.476
- What's going on?

07:56.542 --> 07:58.044
- Um...

07:58.144 --> 08:00.146
Well, I--I came to see you,
sweetheart.

08:00.213 --> 08:07.320
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:08.554 --> 08:10.122
- No, I didn't follow you
into the drug store.

08:10.189 --> 08:11.891
I just happened to be going
to the same place.

08:11.991 --> 08:13.893
- [laughs]
- Okay, I did follow you.

08:13.993 --> 08:15.995
But if you had talked to me
when I pulled up to you

08:16.062 --> 08:17.530
at the red light, then none
of this would have happened.

08:17.630 --> 08:19.365
- In that big red car of yours?
- Mm-hmm.

08:19.465 --> 08:21.300
I looked good, though.
- You did.

08:21.367 --> 08:22.835
You did.
- So did you.

08:22.902 --> 08:25.037
- You were very persistent.
I'll give you that.

08:25.137 --> 08:26.839
[both laugh]

08:26.906 --> 08:30.009
Mia, your father
was such a player.

08:30.076 --> 08:31.711
- Ew.
- What?

08:31.811 --> 08:34.247
- Mia, how's, um--

08:34.347 --> 08:35.681
how's New York?

08:35.748 --> 08:36.916
- It's good.

08:38.217 --> 08:40.319
- Great. Mm.

08:40.386 --> 08:42.655
All right,
I'll leave y'all to it.

08:42.722 --> 08:43.856
[clear throat]

08:43.923 --> 08:46.425
Come here, Mama.
- Okay, Daddy.

08:46.526 --> 08:47.827
- All right.

08:47.894 --> 08:50.029
- [giggles]

08:50.096 --> 08:52.064
- Bye, sweetheart.
[smooches]

08:59.539 --> 09:01.440
- [giggles]
[door shuts]

09:01.541 --> 09:03.676
- What the fuck is going on?

09:04.677 --> 09:07.446
- Mia, don't be upset.

09:07.547 --> 09:09.081
Listen, honey...

09:09.181 --> 09:10.616
[sighs]

09:10.716 --> 09:13.452
Your father and I
have been seeing each other

09:13.553 --> 09:14.954
off and on
for the last few months.

09:15.054 --> 09:17.256
- Is that what
this is all about?

09:17.356 --> 09:18.891
When were you gonna tell me?

09:18.958 --> 09:20.293
- Mia,

09:20.393 --> 09:21.594
I'm on a journey.

09:21.694 --> 09:23.963
- You're always on
some journey, Mom.

09:25.031 --> 09:27.867
Oh, my God, is he the guy
you met up with at Houston's?

09:28.734 --> 09:30.069
- [sighs]

09:30.136 --> 09:31.604
This is all my fault.

09:31.704 --> 09:33.639
I conditioned you
to hate your father.

09:33.739 --> 09:35.708
- Mom, I don't hate him.

09:35.775 --> 09:37.276
I don't know him.

09:37.376 --> 09:39.545
I only saw him, like,
two times a year my whole life.

09:39.612 --> 09:42.148
- That's partially
my fault too.

09:42.248 --> 09:43.649
Mia, honey.

09:43.749 --> 09:46.052
He just wants another chance.

09:48.621 --> 09:50.656
- My mom is fucking my dad.
<i>- What?</i>

09:50.756 --> 09:52.925
- This is, like,
the most self-destructive

09:52.992 --> 09:54.493
shit she's ever done.

09:54.594 --> 09:55.728
<i>- Are they back together?</i>

09:55.795 --> 09:57.463
- I don't know. I hope not.

09:57.563 --> 10:00.733
I'm sorry, but my mom
just has these cycles, and--

10:00.800 --> 10:02.134
<i>- And she's an adult.</i>

10:02.234 --> 10:03.469
<i>I'm sure</i>
<i>she knows what she's doing.</i>

10:03.569 --> 10:04.837
- Jesus.

10:04.937 --> 10:06.439
<i>- If your mom</i>
<i>can forgive your dad,</i>

10:06.505 --> 10:08.474
<i>maybe you should</i>
<i>give him a chance.</i>

10:08.574 --> 10:10.343
- Hey, the TaskRabbit
just pulled up.

10:10.443 --> 10:11.677
I gotta go. I'll call you back.

10:11.777 --> 10:13.646
<i>- Mia, wait.</i>

10:13.746 --> 10:15.448
- Akil?
- Yeah.

10:21.320 --> 10:23.990
<i>narrator: The sight of her</i>
<i>mother and father together</i>

10:24.090 --> 10:25.958
<i>lingered in her mind.</i>

10:26.025 --> 10:30.262
<i>For the past 23 years,</i>
<i>Mia had dutifully supported</i>

10:30.329 --> 10:32.164
<i>and coddled</i>
<i>her eccentric mother</i>

10:32.264 --> 10:36.135
<i>and their united front</i>
<i>against Leon remained intact.</i>

10:42.375 --> 10:45.044
<i>But now her mother had caved,</i>

10:45.144 --> 10:48.547
<i>and Mia couldn't help</i>
<i>but feel betrayed.</i>

11:02.561 --> 11:04.397
- [sobs]

11:11.737 --> 11:14.140
Hey, if it's in a bag,
take it.

11:20.046 --> 11:22.381
[car horn honks]

11:22.481 --> 11:23.916
So, 60?

11:24.016 --> 11:25.818
- Yeah.

11:30.156 --> 11:31.590
Are you okay?

11:31.691 --> 11:32.992
- Yeah.

11:33.059 --> 11:34.593
Those were, uh--
[laughs]

11:34.694 --> 11:37.663
Some good old-fashioned
cleansing tears, you know?

11:38.531 --> 11:40.099
- If you say so.

11:44.437 --> 11:46.272
- Can I bum one?

11:46.372 --> 11:48.541
- Yeah.

11:54.180 --> 11:56.082
- Thanks.

11:56.182 --> 11:58.718
- You should
take my number down.

11:58.784 --> 12:01.387
I mean, just in case
you need me again.

12:01.454 --> 12:03.189
You don't have to use the app.

12:03.255 --> 12:04.757
Can save us both some money.

12:04.857 --> 12:06.559
- Sure.

12:13.399 --> 12:15.434
- Take care of yourself.
- Thanks.

12:17.737 --> 12:19.572
<i>narrator: Mia hadn't had</i>
<i>a real conversation</i>

12:19.638 --> 12:22.041
<i>with her father</i>
<i>in about seven years.</i>

12:22.108 --> 12:24.076
<i>The "out of sight,</i>
<i>out of mind" method</i>

12:24.143 --> 12:25.778
<i>had been working well for her.</i>

12:25.878 --> 12:27.980
<i>But now, thanks to her mother,</i>

12:28.080 --> 12:29.782
<i>she was forced to face him</i>

12:29.882 --> 12:32.585
<i>and all of the memories she</i>
<i>had spent years repressing.</i>

12:32.651 --> 12:35.788
- Hey, honey.
- Hey.

12:35.888 --> 12:37.456
- Enjoy.
- I can't believe my daughter

12:37.556 --> 12:39.158
deals Birkin bags.

12:39.258 --> 12:41.994
I told my sister about your job
and she asked for a hookup,

12:42.094 --> 12:43.229
and I was like,
"Well, you better

12:43.295 --> 12:45.164
hook up about 25 grand first."

12:45.264 --> 12:46.832
- Try 100.
- What?

12:46.932 --> 12:49.668
- Yeah.
- Who's got that kind of money?

12:49.769 --> 12:50.970
[chuckles]

12:51.070 --> 12:53.439
Your mom tells me
you have a boyfriend.

12:53.506 --> 12:55.775
- Sounds like she's really
filling you in, huh?

12:55.841 --> 12:57.109
- She has.

12:57.176 --> 12:59.578
I'm really proud of you.
Always have been.

13:02.515 --> 13:04.817
- Do you remember when you
picked me up in that Corvette?

13:06.786 --> 13:07.753
- Yeah.

13:07.820 --> 13:09.021
Suzanné went off of me.

13:09.121 --> 13:10.456
She almost
didn't let me take you.

13:10.523 --> 13:11.824
- Then you took me
to McDonald's

13:11.924 --> 13:13.359
and I wanted to order
for myself,

13:13.459 --> 13:14.760
but you said we should share.

13:14.827 --> 13:16.662
And then you let me have
two bites of your burger

13:16.762 --> 13:18.297
and four French fries.

13:18.364 --> 13:21.467
Then I dropped one on the floor
and you got mad at me?

13:24.136 --> 13:25.504
- Baby,
I think you're misremembering.

13:25.604 --> 13:27.339
- No, I'm not.

13:27.439 --> 13:29.809
Then you drove me
to your girlfriend's house

